 work with Adam Levine, concerning Heegaard\nFloer homology and the orderability of fundamental groups. Namely, we prove\nthat if $\\widehat{CF}(M)$ is particularly simple, i.e., $M$ is what we call a\n\"strong $L$-space,\" then $\\pi_1(M)$ is not left-orderable.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Jul 2014 03:12:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-07-04"}
