r unitary representation having a\nsubspace $L$ as above.\n  The operator angle between the projection $P_L$ onto $L$ (typically the\ncharacteristic function of the fundamental domain) and the projection $P_0$\nonto the subspace $H_0$ (typically a Bergman projection onto a space of\nanalytic functions), is the analogue of the space of $\\Gamma$- invariant\nvectors.\n  We prove that the character of the unitary representation\n$\\overline{\\pi}^{\\rm{p}}$ is uniquely determined by the character of the\nrepresentation $\\pi$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Jul 2014 12:36:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Aug 2014 19:56:27 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 11 Aug 2014 18:40:54 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 17 Mar 2015 19:54:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-18"}
